		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=257373"><span id=>Djsefnet</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />10 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Djsefnet&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Hey there ubermuse.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am by no means an uber necro, but it's safe to take my advice =p.  I bought all +mana gear for my necro when he was low level, big mistake.  Here's what I did after I farmed some plat to replace his horrible +mana gear: I got myself to 200 int, replaced a few pieces of gear with pieces that had a lot of hp on them, and then after I had as much HP as I could have, and having as close to 200 int as I could have, I got Burning Affliction III, Mana preservation III, and Affliction Haste IV.  Focus effects are very important for a necro, more than HP some say.  I like having my HP really high, and I like having AH since it means if a snare gets resisted thats less cast  time to try to re-snare. Thankfully, most items that have hp for int casters have +mana too either from raw mana or int.  So of your three school of thoughts, ignore the int/mana one and select mana+hp or focus.  If I had my choice of gear from all gear that is in game however, I would pick focus based items first, and then high-hp items.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Monkey spit</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
