		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=FbOooM&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>As everyone else has said here, I would definitely avoid the int/mana train of thought. There's no need to concentrate on it as a necro, especially since you are 1 level away from lich. As for focus effects, if you have GoD, you can help yourself a great deal with getting some nice focus effect items and great experience at your level. <br /><br />First you can do the quest for Kiki's Recipe Book with Mana Preservation III. <br /><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2779" target="akztarg">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=2779</a><br /><br />Second, you can either solo the fierce cragwalker (first time I was successful was at 51) or a lot of times people will /ooc that his loot is rotting since it is lore. He drops a couple different pieces and one is a Thick Netted Veil with Spell Haste III. <br /><br />The added bonus while you are doing this is that you have a chance at getting 1 of the 2 drops that normally sell for 50k because they drop off the mobs that you should be fighting at your level. <br /><br />The robe I bought in the bazaar was the Robe of Misery with Burning Affliction III, which has been my best investment to date. The added damage on your dots is a must when soloing. I don't remember what I paid for the robe but I remember getting a good deal on it compared to a few other prices it was listed at.<br /><br />HP regen is my next target and I started that yesterday by purchasing a Regal Staff of the Court Mortician for 15k.<br /><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17806" target="akztarg">http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=17806</a><br /><br />Please don't forget that Stamina = HP so items with stamina and HP are even better. I think you should be able to find a nice balance between HP, Focus Effects and even HP regen. I think I have done the first 2 and after purchasing the staff yesterday, my intelligence is now maxed at 255 without concentrating on intelligence gear.</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
