		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=222100"><span id=Scholar>emperorjeremy</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="77" width="80" src="/uf/emperorjeremy/irenicus.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />568 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.36]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=emperorjeremy&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Focus gear &gt; All.<br /><br />A close second would be HP and resists.<br />Next would be mana regen.<br />Last would be INT/ mana / hp regen.<br /><br /><br />Of course, it's a situational setup when you're talking focus vs. HP.<br /><br />For raids, foci aren't that important.&nbsp;&nbsp;Most mobs we won't be dotting, or need to nuke quickly on.  Maybe use improved damage.<br />Otherwise, get HP and saves.<br /><br /><br />Soloing, though, you're normally hate kiting (well, when fear stops working), so you can drop much of your HP / save gear and slap on some foci, which are really important the higher up you get.<br /><br />Definitely one I can't live without : Affliction Haste 4<br />Depending on markets, you can get the Ceramic skull of decay, player crafted, for a few K (this varies widely).  Or, you can get the focus through tribute.  It's much better for a necro than Spell Haste will ever be.  At level 65, about 90% of my casting is DoTs.  <br /><br />Another nice one is Affliction Efficiency 4 for saving mana on dots (ceramic gavel of justice).  Burning Affliction 4 is nice, but items for that effect are either raid or very rare (ceramic shackles of torment...super expensive because of component pains), or of course through tribute.<br /><br /><br /><br />Reagent conservation is pretty pointless, unless you like trying to save pet components.  I do keep a royal amulet of Takish on hand (Reagent Conv. 3) for when I cast my rezz or summon corpse spells...though so far, I've had no successes with the item =/<br />If you can remember to swap it out when you cast those spells (not my main neck since the amulet is pretty weak), then maybe it'll save you a tiny coffin or essence emerald one day.<br /><br />Mana Pres. 4 is nice, but not really a deal-breaker.  Mana pres. 4 comes mostly into play on raids (nuking or twitching) or doing Ldons (when mobs usually die too fast for a dot and again you're nuking).<br /><br /><br />I could probably live without all my foci if I HAD to except for affliction haste 4...it's simply that good of a focus.  <br /><br />That being said, my normal setup consists of ::<br /><br />Mana pres 4<br />Spell haste 4<br />Affliction haste 4<br />Affliction Eff. 4<br />Neurosis (neurotoxin mana saver)<br /><br /><br />Edit: I really don't consider HP regen a target at all.  1) I'm a lizard (woot!) and 2) HP DoTs are pretty effective at keeping HP up.<br /><br /><br />Debaucher Soulrender<br />65 Necro, 145AA<br />Rodcet<br /><br /><br /><br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Sat Jun 26 10:16:49 2004 by emperorjeremy</span></i></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://wow.allakhazam.com/profile.html?81601" target="akztarg">Dustmite</a> 48 Mage Extraordinaire<br />Noe the 48 Druid.<br /><br /><br />-----<br />Shop Smart. Shop S-Mart.<br /><br /></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Swampland, USA</td></tr></table>
